figures.alternate_text: Three-panel Venn diagram labeled a, b, and c. Panel a shows a single pink oval with a dashed outline. Panel b displays three overlapping pink ovals with multiple dashed outlines, indicating intersections. Panel c features a larger set of overlapping pink ovals with various dashed and solid outlines, suggesting complex relationships and groupings.

Image showing two panels of a CyberKnife robotic radiosurgery system. Panel (a) depicts a clinical setting with a patient lying on a treatment table, attended by a medical professional. The CyberKnife system is positioned above the patient, ready for treatment. Panel (b) illustrates the robotic arm of the CyberKnife in various positions, demonstrating its range of motion. The system is labeled 'CyberKnife' and is designed for precise, non-invasive treatment. The room is well-lit with a modern design.

Panel figure showing four medical devices. \\n\\n(a) A Medtronic machine with a monitor displaying medical imaging, labeled 'Further Together.'\\n\\n(b) A small gold device with a blue wire and purple ends.\\n\\n(c) A robotic medical device with a monitor showing endoscopic images.\\n\\n(d) A gloved hand holding a flexible, coiled medical instrument.

Close-up images of four different needle tips on a blue textured background, labeled a, b, c, and d. Each needle has a distinct tip shape, with variations in sharpness and length. The images focus on the fine details of the needle tips, highlighting their precision and design differences.

A panel of medical imaging photos showing different diagnostic views of the chest. Image (a) is a CT scan displaying cross-sectional views of the lungs and heart. Images (b) and (c) are fluoroscopic images showing a procedure with visible instruments and contrast material. Image (d) is an ultrasound with a yellow arrow pointing to a specific area. Image (e) is a chest X-ray highlighting areas of interest with white arrows. Each image provides a different perspective for medical analysis.

Three-panel medical imaging figure showing different views of the chest. Panel (a) is a cross-sectional CT scan displaying the heart and lungs, highlighting the internal structures. Panel (b) is a frontal chest X-ray showing the ribcage, spine, and lung fields. Panel (c) is a lateral chest X-ray providing a side view of the thoracic cavity. Each panel is labeled with letters a, b, and c in the top left corner.

Image showing two types of coiled objects. On the left, labeled 'a,' is a gold-colored, tightly wound coil. On the right, labeled 'b,' are three white, cylindrical coils with a similar winding pattern. The image highlights the contrast in color and material between the two sets of coils.

The image is a panel figure with three subfigures labeled a, b, and c. Subfigure a shows a vial labeled 'BioXmark' with a clear liquid inside. Subfigure b depicts a close-up of a dropper releasing a droplet onto a surface. Subfigure c consists of three medical imaging scans, likely CT scans, showing cross-sectional views of a human chest with highlighted areas marked by colored lines. The scans display anatomical structures in black and white.
